FBIS4-41409 "drsov122_b_94022" FBIS-SOV-94-122 Daily Report 24 Jun 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Economic Issues Inflation Drops to 6.9 Percent Inflation Drops to 6.9 Percent LD2406132394 Moscow Radio Moscow World Service in English 1100 GMT 24 Jun 94 LD2406132394 Moscow Radio Moscow World Service English BFN [Text] Russia's state statistical service has reviewed the country's development in the first six months of the year. It says that a kind of record was set. Inflation dropped to the lowest level in all of the two and a half years of reform. It amounted to 6.9 percent. At the same time, through tough financial measures, the government has been able to slow down the growth of prices. But as the government experts say, it is too early to celebrate victory. In the same period there's been a record high bank emission. Almost four trillion more rubles were put into circulation. Experts say that such a big wave of money that are not backed by commodities or services could tell on the home market in two or three months.
